    (2, 6, 'Case Study - Queen Elizabeth II', 'The longest-reigning British monarch. Need we say more?', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"The Longest-Reigning British Monarch. Ever", "Became ruler in her 20s", "Has a likeable, humorous personality", "Has answered millions of correspondences from citizens", "Lover of corgis and charities"}', FALSE),
    (2, 7, 'Case Study - George Washington', 'The man, the legend. First president and founding father', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"The Man, the Legend. First President and Founding Father", "Contrary to popular belief, did not have wooden teeth", "Demonstrated exemplary character and conviction", "Treated others with dignity and respect", "Truly cared about his people, leading to loyalty"}', FALSE),
    (2, 8, 'Tying It All Together', 'What can we learn from these leaders? How can you become like them?', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"What Can We Learn from These Leaders?", "Let people see your vision", "Be likeable and keep in touch with those you lead", "Care about others and treat them well"}', FALSE),
    (2, 9, 'Introspection and Improvement', 'How to apply these principles to your own strengths and weaknesses', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"How to Apply These Principles to You", "Know thyself", "Be honest with your own strengths and weaknesses", "Identify overlaps and synergies", "Take it one lesson at a time"}', FALSE),
    (2, 10, 'Key Takeaways', 'Rome wasn''t built in a day. Learn things you can do daily to get there', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Rome Wasn''t Built in a Day. Learn Things You Can Do Daily to Get There", "Uncover what you want to work on", "Work on one thing at a time", "Reflect after every opportunity"}', FALSE),
    (3, 1, 'How Your Thoughts Affect You', 'Your brain makes conclusions that aren''t true. Learn to trick that tricky trickster', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Just How Powerful Is the Mind?", "Your mood is affected by your thoughts", "Your mind sometimes does its own thing", "When thoughts arise, learn to recognize them", "Recognize them to learn to control them", "Control them to control your happiness"}', FALSE),
    (3, 2, 'Perceptions of Reality and Distortions', 'Your mind distorts everything', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"How Your Brain Distorts Everything", "Sound travels way slower than light", "And the images your eyes capture are upside-down and backwards", "So your brain is constantly distorting reality to make sense of it", "Everything gets distorted for its purpose", "Accept that and embrace it"}', FALSE),
    (3, 3, 'Identifying Harmful Thoughts', 'Learn to recognize those bad thoughts', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Learning to Identify the Bad Thoughts", "Unwanted thoughts will happen", "Learn to monitor all your thoughts", "Evaluate thoughts against your values", "Write down your thoughts and try to read them from a third person perspective"}', FALSE),
    (3, 4, 'Differentiating Misperceptions From Reality', 'Separate fact from fiction', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Separating Fact from Fiction", "Start a journal", "Write down your thoughts and feelings in free form", "Read your entries when not emotionally charged", "Learn the distorted lies your brain is telling you"}', FALSE),
    (3, 5, 'Challenging and Overcoming Negativity', 'Overcome and remove negativity in your life', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Overcome and Remove Negativity in Your Life", "Now you''ve discovered some of your negative thoughts", "Removing them is key to removing negativity in your life", "Know that you are stronger than your thoughts", "Start by telling yourself that your negative thoughts are lies", "Move on to stifling these thoughts"}', FALSE),
    (3, 6, 'Coping and Relaxation', 'Frankie says relax', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Frankie Says Relax", "Relax don''t do it", "When you want to go to it", "Relax don''t do it,", "When you want to come"}', FALSE),
    (3, 7, 'Managing Stress and Being Resilient', 'Stress happens. Learn to judo it', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Stress Is Inevitable. Learning to Live with It", "Stress will happen", "Remember that diamonds are created from pressure", "All things must pass", "Most problems aren''t big problems", "Ask yourself if the problem will still be a problem in 5 minutes, 5 hours, 5 days, 5 weeks, 5 months, 5 years", "Don''t trouble yourself with small problems"}', FALSE),
    (3, 8, 'Making The Right Changes Daily', 'One step at a time, one day at a time', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"One Step at a Time, One Day at a Time", "Every day is a new opportunity", "You will win some and lose some", "The important thing is progress", "Compare yourself to past you and not others"}', FALSE),
    (4, 1, 'What to Expect As a New Parent', 'This might be harder than you think. Here are some of the things you can expect', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Setting Your Expectations", "Your baby will make you cry", "Take breaks as you need them", "Remember that countless people raised children without the luxuries you have today", "Your parents, their parents, and every one of their parents before them were able to do this", "As hard as this may get, it will pass", "Savor this time you have with them- they''ll grow so big before you know it"}', FALSE),
    (4, 2, 'How to Not Go Crazy From Sleep Deprivation', 'You will be sleep deprived as part of being a new parent. Here''s how you can manage that somewhat', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"How to Manage Sleep Deprivation", "Sleep deprivation is literally torture as defined by the Geneva Conventions", "Don''t sell yourself short", "It is hard but nothing you can''t overcome", "Learn to sleep when your baby sleeps", "Your body will adjust to naps"}', FALSE),
    (4, 3, 'Tackling The Hardship With Your Partner', 'You outnumber your baby 2 to 1. Learn how to divide and conquer!', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"You Outnumber Your Baby 2 to 1. Learning to Divide and Conquer", "Take turns", "Sharing is caring", "Specialize in certain tasks but trade off", "Maintain a partnership", "Each partner should try to put in 60%", "Don''t keep track of how much more you do", "Keep open communications and don''t build resentment"}', FALSE),
    (4, 4, 'Getting Help From Your Network of Friends and Family', 'Everybody loves babies. Use this to your advantage when you need a night away', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Everybody Loves Babies. Use This to Your Advantage", "Don''t be afraid to ask for help", "It takes a village to raise a child", "People will want to help you", "It is OK to not do everything yourselves"}', FALSE),
    (5, 1, 'Active Listening', 'You can''t learn when your mouth is open. How to embrace silence', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"You Can''t Learn When You''re Talking. That''s a Fact", "Listening is underrated", "People love talking about themselves", "People will want to talk to you when they feel good talking to you", "People will forget what you said, but will remember how you made them feel"}', FALSE),
    (5, 2, 'LES is More - Listen, Empathize, Speak', 'First listen, then empathize, and only after, speak', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"First Listen, Then Empathize, and Only After, Speak", "Listening should be step one", "You can''t communicate with someone if you don''t hear what they''re saying", "After hearing them out, empathize and understand", "Only once you understand, you can talk about relevant things and ask questions", "Talk only to contribute to the conversation"}', FALSE),
    (5, 3, 'How to Articulate Your Feelings', 'It is hard to convey your thoughts and feelings', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Conveying Your Thoughts and Feelings the Right Way", "What you say and what they hear may not be the same", "Take care not to alienate or upset the listener", "Try to understand their point of view and how they''re receiving what you''re sending", "Learn to filter what you say before blurting out what immediately comes to mind"}', FALSE),
    (5, 4, 'Fostering Bilateral Communication', 'Communication is an art, with some science you can use', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Communication is an Art, With Some Science You Can Use", "Communication has to be a 2-way street", "Your goal is not to convince them or argue", "Practice, practice, practice", "Some people are naturally more effective communicators, but remember that hard work beats talent when talent doesn''t work hard"}', FALSE),
    (6, 1, 'Working Out Is Great #1', 'You will feel better, sleep better, look better, and bonus: you''ll be better prepared for a zombie apocalypse', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Why You Should Maintain and Train Your Body", "Dopamine and endorphines, oh my!", "Working out results in better quality of sleep", "You will feel better in your day to day because you will have more energy and a way to destress", "If there''s a zombie apocalypse, you will have a much higher chance of survival", "Motivating yourself to go to the gym is the hardest part", "Motivation is fickle. Cultivate discipline instead"}', FALSE),
    (6, 2, 'Working Out Is Great #2', 'The sooner you start, the longer you can reap all the benefits. It gets harder the longer you wait', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"The Best Time to Plant a Tree is 20 Years Ago. The Next Best Time is Today", "The sooner you start, the longer you will have all the benefits in your life", "The longer you wait, the harder it gets to start", "Maintaining your body is much easier than training your body and reversing years of bad habits", "Working out is a great equalizer", "You have to put in the work and there are no shortcuts", "You will see your body improve over time as a direct result of your efforts"}', FALSE),
    (6, 3, 'Garbage In, Garbage Out', 'You are what you eat. Learn to eat more healthily', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"You Are What You Eat", "Food is fuel for your body", "If you wouldn''t put cheap bad gas in your car, why would you do the same for your body?", "Good diet leads to better sleep, more energy, better skin", "Remember it''s not binary- give yourself some leeway to eat your favorite foods", "Don''t think about it as a diet, but rather a lifestyle choice"}', FALSE),
    (6, 4, 'Treating Your Body With Love and Kindness', 'Learn to take care of this shell you''re stuck with', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/IMG_0729-2.jpg', '{"Tips to Taking Care of Your Body (So It Can Take Care of You)", "You get one body so treat it like a precious thing", "It''s a marathon, not a sprint", "Good things take time", "Daily work adds up over time", "Work on your trends and habits, not dwell on single points of failure", "Diet + Exercise = Better mind and body", "Future you will be grateful for everything you do today"}', FALSE);
